## Plan Summary

**Root cause:** Off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts` — the `processItems` loop condition reads `i < items.length - 1`, which stops one step short, skipping the last element every time. For a single-element array, nothing runs at all.

**The fix is a one-character change on line 7:**

```typescript
// Before (buggy)
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {

// After (fixed)
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
```

**Impact:** 3 of 4 tests in `tests/utils.test.ts` are currently failing. After removing the `- 1`, all 4 will pass.

Approve the plan to proceed with the fix?

